nd natural scientists, environmentalists and economists, architects and planners -- to discuss topics such as sustainable natural resource use and urbanization, industrial and technological development, economy and politics, history and geography.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aEconomic developmentxEnvironmental aspectsxPersian Gulf States. 0aEconomic developmentxEnvironmental aspectszPersian Gulf States. 0aEnvironmental policyxPersian Gulf States. 0aEnvironmental policyzPersian Gulf States. 0aSustainable developmentxGovernment policyxPersian Gulf Region. 0aSustainable developmentxGovernment policyzPersian Gulf Region. 0aSustainable developmentxPersian Gulf Region. 0aSustainable developmentzPersian Gulf Region. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh1 aAl Othman, Wesam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAl-Ghanim, Kaltham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAl-Khalaqi, Aziza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAl-Khulaifi, Najla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAl-Misnad, Sheikha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlmannai, Salah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlraouf, Ali A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlshawi, Ali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampbell, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Sarah F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConingham, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarwish, Bahaa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 